com.ibm.avatar.api

Class CompileAQLParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.avatar.api.CompileAQLParams
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class CompileAQLParams
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    This class encapsulates all parameters needed for compiling modular and non-modular AQL. Construct an instance of this class and pass it as parameter to CompileAQL.compile(CompileAQLParams).
    This class provides a constructor for the common scenario when the input non-modular AQL is in a file and the output compiled module should be written to a location specified by the output URI.

      • CompileAQLParams

        public CompileAQLParams()
        Create a parameter container with default values.

      • CompileAQLParams

        public CompileAQLParams(File inputFile,
                        String outputURI,
                        String dataPath)
        Create a parameter container for the common scenario when the input non-modular AQL is in a file and the output compiled module is to be written to a location specified by the output URI.
        Parameters:
        inputFile - Top-level non-modular AQL file
        outputURI - Output URI where the compiled module will be placed. Should point to a valid directory or JAR/ZIP file on the local filesystem. See Supported URI Formats for details.
        dataPath - Path for finding auxiliary dictionary, AQL, and UDF files, or NULL to use the parent directory of the top-level input AQL file. The path can contain multiple directories, separated by the character ';'. The path separator character is ';' regardless of platform.

      • CompileAQLParams

        public CompileAQLParams(String[] inputModules,
                        String outputURI,
                        String modulePath)
                 throws Exception
        Create a parameter container for the common scenario when the input AQL is a set of modules and the compiled representation of those modules (.tam files) are sent to a directory or a .jar/.zip archive file. Use either setTokenizerConfig(TokenizerConfig) or setTokenizer(Tokenizer) to indicate the type of tokenizer to use when compiling dictionaries.
        Parameters:
        inputModules - array of URIs pointing to the root directories of module source code on the local filesystem; one entry per module. See Supported URI Formats for details.
        outputURI - path to directory or .jar/.zip file on the local file system where the compiled module representation (.tam file) of each input module is sent to. See Supported URI Formats for details.
        modulePath - list, separated by semi-colon (;), of paths to directories or .jar/.zip files where the compiled representation (.tam) of modules referenced in the input modules are to be found. Compiled modules are searched for only inside directories specified in this path.
        Throws:
        Exception

      • CompileAQLParams

        public CompileAQLParams(String[] inputModules,
                        String outputURI,
                        String modulePath,
                        TokenizerConfig tokenizerCfg)
                 throws Exception
        Create a parameter container for the common scenario when the input AQL is a set of modules, the compiled representation of those modules (.tam files) are sent to a directory or a .jar/.zip archive file, and you wish to use a specific tokenizer configuration for compiling dictionaries.
        Parameters:
        inputModules - array of URIs pointing to the root directories of module source code on the local filesystem; one entry per module. See Supported URI Formats for details.
        outputURI - path to directory or .jar/.zip file on the local file system where the compiled module representation (.tam file) of each input module is sent to. See Supported URI Formats for details.
        modulePath - list, separated by semi-colon (;), of paths to directories or .jar/.zip files where the compiled representation (.tam) of modules referenced in the input modules are to be found. Compiled modules are searched for only inside directories specified in this path.
        tokenizerCfg - tokenization configuration to be used while compiling internal dictionaries; if null is passed, this method will create a Standard tokenizer by default
        Throws:
        Exception

      • setPerformSDM

        public void setPerformSDM(Boolean flag)
        Enable or disable the Shared Dictionary Matching (SDM) optimization. When enabled, the Text Analytics optimizer determines all cases where more than one dictionary is evaluated against a given source text and evaluates each of those sets of dictionaries together in one pass over the source text. Improves the throughput of the extractor.
        Parameters:
        flag - true to enable the Shared Dictionary Matching (SDM) optimization. true by default.

      • getPerformSDM

        public Boolean getPerformSDM()
        Return whether the Shared Dictionary Matching (SDM) optimization is enabled.
        Returns:
        true if Shared Dictionary Matching (SDM) is enabled.

      • setPerformRSR

        public void setPerformRSR(Boolean flag)
        Enable or disable the Regex Strength Reduction (RSR) optimization. When enabled, the Text Analytics Optimizer uses the Text Analytics Runtime built-in fast regex (SimpleRegex) engine when possible, instead of the Java regex engine. Improves the throughput of the extractor, but may also increase memory footprint.
        Parameters:
        flag - true to enable Regex Strength Reduction (RSR). true by default.

      • getPerformRSR

        public Boolean getPerformRSR()
        Return whether the Regex Strength Reduction (RSR) optimization is enabled.
        Returns:
        true if Regex Strength Reduction (RSR) is enabled.

      • getPerformSRM

        public final boolean getPerformSRM()

        Returns:
        true if Shared Regex Matching (SRM) is enabled.

      • setPerformSRM

        public final void setPerformSRM(boolean flag)
        Enable or disable the Shared Regex Matching (SRM) optimization. When enabled, the Text Analytics Optimizer determines all compatible regular expressions over a given input view and evaluates all of them at the same time. Improves the throughput of the extractor.
        Parameters:
        flag - true to enable Regex Strength Reduction (RSR). true by default.

      • setDataPath

        public final void setDataPath(String dataPath)
        Set the path for finding auxiliary dictionary, AQL, and UDF files, or NULL to use the parent directory of the top-level input AQL file. The path can contain multiple directories, separated by the character ';'. The path separator character is ';' regardless of platform. The dataPath parameter is used only when compiling non-modular AQL.
        Parameters:
        dataPath - string containing one or more directory paths separated by ';' regardless of platform, or null to use the parent directory of the top-level input file when input file is not null, or when there are no auxiliary files.

        public void setOutputURI(String outputURI)

        Sets the URI where compiler should store the compiled modules. This URI should point to an existing directory, or a JAR/ZIP file on local filesystem. See Supported URI Formats for details. The modules specified through setInputModules(String[]) are compiled into <moduleName>.tam and placed into the location represented by the outputURI parameter.

      • setModulePath

        public void setModulePath(String modulePath)
                   throws Exception
        Sets the path where the compiler can locate pre-compiled .tam files of the dependent modules, while compiling the input modules. This path is a semicolon-separated list of file:// or hdfs:// URIs that refer to absolute paths of locations where dependent modules can be located. Each entry in the modulePath can be either a directory (or) a JAR/ZIP file containing compiled modules (i.e., .tam files). See Supported URI Formats for details.
        Parameters:
        modulePath - semicolon-separated list of URIs on local or distributed filesystem that refer to absolute paths of locations where dependent modules can be located; null, if the modules to compile are not dependent on any other modules.
        Throws:
        Exception

      • validate

        public void validate()
              throws InvalidCompileParamException
        Validates the parameters passed to the compiler. The following validation rules are enforced:
        1. Provide only one of the following parameters: inputFile, inputStr, inputModules.
        2. Only one of the input parameters listed above must be provided. They are mutually exclusive.
        3. When compiling modular AQLs, the inputModules array should be non-null and have at least one entry.
        4. The outputURI parameter must point to an existing directory (or) a JAR/ZIP file.
        Throws:
        InvalidCompileParamException - if there is any validation error

      • isBackwardCompatibilityMode

        public boolean isBackwardCompatibilityMode()
        Returns true if the given compilation parameters makes the compiler run in backward-compatibility mode; returns false otherwise. The compiler will run in backward-compatibility mode, if the input modules are NOT provided by invoking setInputModules(String[]).
        Returns:
        true, if the given compilation parameters make the compiler run in backward-compatibility mode;false otherwise

      • normalizeURI

        @Deprecated
public static String normalizeURI(String origPath)
                                       throws Exception
        Deprecated. This function will be removed in later releases
        Returns a normalized URI string. The following normalizations are performed:
        1) URIs with missing schema are assumed to be pointing to the local filesystem.
        2) A trailing '/' character is appended to URIs pointing to the directory, which already does not contains one.
        In addition to normalization, this method also validates the given URI string for syntax(format of URI); it does not validates the existence of the URI's target.
        Parameters:
        origPath - a raw URI passed into the params object
        Returns:
        normalized and validated URI
        Throws:
        Exception - if the URI can't be validated
